cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which are typically covered by the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep neural network learners and cross-lingual word embeddings suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the development of evaluation datasets, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
